node.text: New Zealand police have shot and killed an ISIS supporter who injured at least six people in a supermarket “terrorist attack” in the Auckland suburb of New Lynn on Friday, authorities say. Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern said that the man was a Sri Lankan national, a “supporter of ISIS ideology,” and a “known security threat.” He was under constant surveillance by multiple government agencies, and security personnel were able to kill him within 60 seconds from the start of the knife attack, she said. Three of the people who were injured are in a critical condition. (📸: Fiona Goodall/Getty Images)
